    h2.flex-center.flex-justify
      span(translate="Why Bitcoin?")
    .flex-row.flex-start.flex-between.mbl
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="What makes Bitcoin different?")
        p.phl Bitcoin is an anonymous, decentralized currency that was created in 2008. It relies on the blockchain, a public ledger that records bitcoin transactions, instead of central banks.
          a(href="http://www.coindesk.com/information/what-is-bitcoin/" translate="More info.")
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="Where can I use Bitcoin?")
        p.phl You can use Bitcoin at thousands of online stores, or send money around the world to friends and family for a miniscule fee.
          a(href="https://www.bitcoin.com/spend-bitcoin-online" translate="Find stores.")
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="What determines Bitcoin's Price?")
        p.phl Supply and Demand determines the price of Bitcoin, and its value is backed by mathematics.
          a(href="https://bitcoin.org/en/faq#why-do-bitcoins-have-value" translate="More info.")

    h2.flex-center.flex-justify
      span(translate="Blockchain Wallet Features")
    .flex-row.flex-start.flex-between.mbvl
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="HD Addresses")
        p.phl We have your privacy in mind which is why we use HD addresses to avoid address reuse for increased privacy.
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="You control your key")
        p.phl Blockchain never controls your private keys. We encrypt everything before safely storing it on our servers. This is nothing new for our Legacy users.
          a(href="https://blockchain.info/wallet/how-it-works") How it works.
      .flex-1.flex-center.flex-column.center
        h4(translate="Dynamic Fees")
        p.phl We adjust fees for you based on the current network conditions and the size of your transaction. More advanced users can also set their own custom fees.

